M|finance-metrics-quickref|Quick reference for any SaaS fin metric without deep teaching. Use this when you need a fast formula lookup, benchmark check, or dec framework reminder. For detailed explanations, calculations, and ex
M|finance-metrics-quickref|This is not a teaching tool—it's a cheat sheet optimized for speed. Scan, find, apply.
M|finance-metrics-quickref|Metrics are organized into four families:
M|finance-metrics-quickref|1. **Revenue & Growth** — Top-line money (revenue, ARPU, ARPA, MRR/ARR, churn, NRR, expansion)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|2. **Unit Economics** — Customer-level profitability (CAC, LTV, payback, margins)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|3. **Capital Efficiency** — Cash management (burn rate, runway, OpEx, net income)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|4. **Efficiency Ratios** — Growth vs. profitability balance (Rule of 40, magic number)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Use this when:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- You need a quick formula or benchmark
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- You're preparing for a board meeting or investor call
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- You're evaluating a dec and need to check which metrics matter
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- You want to identify red flags quickly
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Don't use this when:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- You need detailed calculation guidance (use `saas-revenue-growth-metrics` or `saas-economics-efficiency-metrics`)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- You're learning these metrics for the first time (start with deep-dive skills)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- You need examples and common pitfalls (covered in related skills)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Metric** | **Formula** | **What It Measures** | **Good Benchmark** | **Red Flag** |
M|finance-metrics-quickref||------------|-------------|----------------------|-------------------|--------------|
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Revenue** | Total sales before expenses | Top-line money earned | Growth rate >20% YoY (varies by stage) | Revenue growing slower than costs |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **ARPU** | Total Revenue / Total Users | Revenue per individual user | Varies by model; track trend | ARPU declining cohort-over-cohort |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **ARPA** | MRR / Active Accounts | Revenue per customer account | SMB: $100-$1K; Mid: $1K-$10K; Ent: $10K+ | High ARPA + low ARPU (undermonetized seats) |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **ACV** | Annual Recurring Revenue per Contract | Annualized contract value | SMB: $5K-$25K; Mid: $25K-$100K; Ent: $100K+ | ACV declining (moving downmarket unintentionally) |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **MRR/ARR** | MRR × 12 = ARR | Predictable recurring revenue | Growth + quality matter; track components | New MRR declining while churn stable/growing |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Churn Rate** | Customers Lost / Starting Customers | % of customers who cancel | Monthly <2% great, <5% ok; Annual <10% great | Churn increasing cohort-over-cohort |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **NRR** | (Start ARR + Expansion - Churn - Contraction) / Start ARR × 100 | Revenue retention + expansion | >120% excellent; 100-120% good; 90-100% ok | NRR <100% (base is contracting) |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Expansion Revenue** | Upsells + Cross-sells + Usage Growth | Additional revenue from existing customers | 20-30% of total revenue | Expansion <10% of MRR |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Quick Ratio** | (New MRR + Expansion MRR) / (Churned MRR + Contraction) | Revenue gains vs. losses | >4 excellent; 2-4 healthy; <2 leaky bucket | Quick Ratio <2 (leaky bucket) |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Gross Margin** | (Revenue - COGS) / Revenue × 100 | % of revenue after direct costs | SaaS: 70-85% good; <60% concerning | Gross margin <60% or declining |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **CAC** | Total S&M Spend / New Customers | Cost to acquire one customer | Varies: Ent $10K+ ok; SMB <$500 | CAC increasing while LTV flat |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **LTV** | ARPU × Gross Margin % / Churn Rate | Total revenue from one customer | Must be 3x+ CAC; varies by segment | LTV declining cohort-over-cohort |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **LTV:CAC** | LTV / CAC | Unit economics efficiency | 3:1 healthy; <1:1 unsustainable; >5:1 underinvesting | LTV:CAC <1.5:1 |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Payback Period** | CAC / (Monthly ARPU × Gross Margin %) | Months to recover CAC | <12 months great; 12-18 ok; >24 concerning | Payback >24 months (cash trap) |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Contribution Margin** | (Revenue - All Variable Costs) / Revenue × 100 | True contribution after variable costs | 60-80% good for SaaS; <40% concerning | Contribution margin <40% |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Burn Rate** | Monthly Cash Spent - Revenue | Cash consumed per month | Net burn <$200K manageable early; <$500K growth | Net burn accelerating |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Runway** | Cash Balance / Monthly Net Burn | Months until money runs out | 12+ months good; 6-12 ok; <6 crisis | Runway <6 months |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **OpEx** | S&M + R&D + G&A | Costs to run the business | Should grow slower than revenue | OpEx growing faster than revenue |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Net Income** | Revenue - All Expenses | Actual profit/loss | Early negative ok; mature 10-20%+ margin | Losses accelerating without growth |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Rule of 40** | Revenue Growth % + Profit Margin % | Balance of growth vs. efficiency | >40 healthy; 25-40 ok; <25 concerning | Rule of 40 <25 |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Magic Number** | (Q Revenue - Prev Q Revenue) × 4 / Prev Q S&M | S&M efficiency | >0.75 efficient; 0.5-0.75 ok; <0.5 fix GTM | Magic Number <0.5 |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Operating Leverage** | Revenue Growth vs. OpEx Growth | Scaling efficiency | Revenue growth > OpEx growth | OpEx growing faster than revenue |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Gross vs. Net Revenue** | Net = Gross - Discounts - Refunds - Credits | What you actually keep | Refunds <10%; discounts <20% | Refunds >10% (product problem) |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Revenue Concentration** | Top N Customers / Total Revenue | Dependency on largest customers | Top customer <10%; Top 10 <40% | Top customer >25% (existential risk) |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Revenue Mix** | Product/Segment Revenue / Total Revenue | Portfolio composition | No single product >60% ideal | Single product >80% (no diversification) |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Cohort Analysis** | Group customers by join date; track behavior | Whether business improving or degrading | Recent cohorts same/better than old | Newer cohorts perform worse |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **CAC Payback by Channel** | CAC / Monthly Contribution (by channel) | Payback by acquisition channel | Compare across channels | One channel far worse than others |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Gross Margin Payback** | CAC / (Monthly ARPU × Gross Margin %) | Payback using actual profit | Typically 1.5-2x simple payback | Payback using margin >36 months |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Unit Economics** | Revenue per unit - Cost per unit | Profitability of each "unit" | Positive contribution required | Negative contribution margin |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Segment Payback** | CAC / Monthly Contribution (by segment) | Payback by customer segment | Compare to allocate resources | One segment unprofitable |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Incrementality** | Revenue caused by action - Baseline | True impact of mkt/promo | Measure with holdout tests | Celebrating revenue that would've happened anyway |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Working Capital** | Cash timing between revenue and collection | Cash vs. revenue timing | Annual upfront > monthly billing | Long payment terms killing runway |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|Use these frameworks to combine metrics for common PM decisions.
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Ask:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|1. **Revenue impact?** Direct (pricing, add-on) or indirect (retention, conversion)?
M|finance-metrics-quickref|2. **Margin impact?** What's the COGS? Does it dilute margins?
M|finance-metrics-quickref|3. **ROI?** Revenue impact / dev cost
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Build if:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- ROI >3x in year one (direct monetization), OR
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- LTV impact >10x dev cost (retention), OR
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Strategic value overrides short-term ROI
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Don't build if:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Negative contribution margin even with optimistic adoption
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Payback period exceeds average customer lifetime
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Metrics to check:** Revenue, Gross Margin, LTV, Contribution Margin
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Ask:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|1. **Unit economics?** CAC, LTV, LTV:CAC ratio
M|finance-metrics-quickref|2. **Cash efficiency?** Payback period
M|finance-metrics-quickref|3. **Customer quality?** Cohort retention, NRR by channel
M|finance-metrics-quickref|4. **Scalability?** Magic Number, addressable volume
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Scale if:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- LTV:CAC >3:1 AND
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Payback <18 months AND
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Customer quality meets/beats other channels AND
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Magic Number >0.75
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Don't scale if:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- LTV:CAC <1.5:1 AND
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- No clear path to improvement
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Metrics to check:** CAC, LTV, LTV:CAC, Payback Period, NRR, Magic Number
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Ask:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|1. **ARPU/ARPA impact?** Will revenue per customer increase?
M|finance-metrics-quickref|2. **Conversion impact?** Help or hurt trial-to-paid conversion?
M|finance-metrics-quickref|3. **Churn impact?** Create churn risk or reduce it?
M|finance-metrics-quickref|4. **NRR impact?** Enable expansion or create contraction?
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Implement if:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Net revenue impact positive after churn risk
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Can test with segment before broad rollout
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Don't change if:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- High churn risk without offsetting expansion
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Can't test hypothesis before committing
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Metrics to check:** ARPU, ARPA, Churn Rate, NRR, CAC Payback
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Check by stage:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Early Stage (Pre-$10M ARR):**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Growth Rate >50% YoY
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- LTV:CAC >3:1
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Gross Margin >70%
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Runway >12 months
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Growth Stage ($10M-$50M ARR):**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Growth Rate >40% YoY
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- NRR >100%
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Rule of 40 >40
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Magic Number >0.75
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Scale Stage ($50M+ ARR):**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Growth Rate >25% YoY
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- NRR >110%
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Rule of 40 >40
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Profit Margin >10%
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Metrics to check:** Revenue Growth, NRR, LTV:CAC, Rule of 40, Magic Number, Gross Margin
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Red Flag** | **What It Means** | **Action** |
M|finance-metrics-quickref||--------------|-------------------|------------|
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Churn increasing cohort-over-cohort | Product-market fit degrading | Stop scaling acquisition; fix retention first |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| NRR <100% | Base is contracting | Fix expansion or reduce churn before scaling |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Revenue churn > logo churn | Losing big customers | Investigate why high-value customers leave |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Quick Ratio <2 | Leaky bucket (barely outpacing losses) | Fix retention before scaling acquisition |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Expansion revenue <10% of MRR | No upsell/cross-sell engine | Build expansion paths |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Revenue concentration >50% in top 10 customers | Existential dependency risk | Diversify customer base |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Red Flag** | **What It Means** | **Action** |
M|finance-metrics-quickref||--------------|-------------------|------------|
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| LTV:CAC <1.5:1 | Buying revenue at a loss | Reduce CAC or increase LTV before scaling |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Payback >24 months | Cash trap (long cash recovery) | Negotiate annual upfront or reduce CAC |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Gross margin <60% | Low profitability per dollar | Increase prices or reduce COGS |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| CAC increasing while LTV flat | Unit economics degrading | Optimize conversion or reduce sales cycle |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Contribution margin <40% | Unprofitable after variable costs | Cut variable costs or increase prices |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| **Red Flag** | **What It Means** | **Action** |
M|finance-metrics-quickref||--------------|-------------------|------------|
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Runway <6 months | Survival crisis | Raise capital immediately or cut burn |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Net burn accelerating without revenue growth | Burning faster without results | Cut costs or increase revenue urgency |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| OpEx growing faster than revenue | Negative operating leverage | Freeze hiring; optimize spend |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Rule of 40 <25 | Burning cash without growth | Improve growth or cut to profitability |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|| Magic Number <0.5 | S&M engine broken | Fix GTM efficiency before scaling spend |
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Prioritizing features:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Revenue impact → Revenue, ARPU, Expansion Revenue
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Margin impact → Gross Margin, Contribution Margin
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- ROI → LTV impact, dev cost
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Evaluating channels:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Acquisition cost → CAC, CAC by Channel
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Customer value → LTV, NRR by Channel
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Payback → Payback Period, CAC Payback by Channel
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Scalability → Magic Number
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Pricing decisions:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Monetization → ARPU, ARPA, ACV
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Impact → Churn Rate, NRR, Expansion Revenue
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Efficiency → CAC Payback (will pricing change affect it?)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Business health:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Growth → Revenue Growth, MRR/ARR Growth
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Retention → Churn Rate, NRR, Quick Ratio
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Economics → LTV:CAC, Payback Period, Gross Margin
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Efficiency → Rule of 40, Magic Number, Operating Leverage
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Survival → Burn Rate, Runway
M|finance-metrics-quickref|**Board/investor reporting:**
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Key metrics: ARR, Revenue Growth %, NRR, LTV:CAC, Rule of 40, Magic Number, Burn Rate, Runway
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Stage-specific: Early stage emphasize growth + unit economics; Growth stage emphasize Rule of 40 + Magic Number; Scale stage emphasize profitability + efficiency
M|finance-metrics-quickref|You are deciding whether to build a premium export feature.
M|finance-metrics-quickref|1. Use Framework 1 (Should We Build This Feature?)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|2. Pull baseline metrics: ARPU, Gross Margin, LTV, Contribution Margin
M|finance-metrics-quickref|3. Model optimistic, base, and downside adoption
M|finance-metrics-quickref|4. Reject if contribution margin turns negative in downside case
M|finance-metrics-quickref|Quick output:
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Base case ROI: 3.8x
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Contribution margin impact: +4 points
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- dec: Build now, with a 90-day post-launch check on churn and expansion
M|finance-metrics-quickref|Paid soc is generating many signups but weak retention.
M|finance-metrics-quickref|1. Use Framework 2 (Should We Scale This Acquisition Channel?)
M|finance-metrics-quickref|2. Check CAC, LTV:CAC, Payback Period, and NRR by channel
M|finance-metrics-quickref|3. Compare against best-performing channel, not company average
M|finance-metrics-quickref|Quick output:
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- LTV:CAC: 1.6:1
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Payback: 26 months
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- NRR: 88%
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- dec: Do not scale; cap spend and run targeted optimization tests
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Using blended company averages instead of cohort or channel-level metrics
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Scaling acquisition when Quick Ratio is weak and retention is deteriorating
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Treating high LTV:CAC as sufficient without checking payback and runway impact
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Raising prices based on ARPU lift alone without modeling churn and contraction
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Comparing benchmarks across mismatched company stages or business models
M|finance-metrics-quickref|- Tracking many metrics without a clear dec question
